Composition of functions

Approximate complicated functions

x <- seq(0,2,length.out=1000)
y <- sin(2*pi*x^2)
plot(x,y,type="l")

Single hidden layer

model <- keras_model_sequential()
layer_dense(model,units=100,activation='relu',input_shape=c(1))
layer_dense(model,units=1,activation='linear')
compile(model,loss="mean_squared_error",optimizer="nadam")
history <- fit(model,x,y,batch_size=50,epochs=5000,verbose=0)

summary(model)
## ___________________________________________________________________________
## Layer (type)                     Output Shape                  Param #     
## ===========================================================================
## dense_1 (Dense)                  (None, 100)                   200         
## ___________________________________________________________________________
## dense_2 (Dense)                  (None, 1)                     101         
## ===========================================================================
## Total params: 301
## Trainable params: 301
## Non-trainable params: 0
## ___________________________________________________________________________
plot(x,y,type="l")
lines(x,predict(model,x),col="blue",lty=2)

Two hidden layers

model <- keras_model_sequential()
layer_dense(model,units=20,activation='relu',input_shape=c(1))
layer_dense(model,units=100,activation='relu')
layer_dense(model,units=1,activation='linear')
compile(model,loss="mean_squared_error",optimizer="nadam")
history <- fit(model,x,y,batch_size=50,epochs=5000,verbose=0)

Composite of functions

model <- keras_model_sequential()
layer_dense(model,units=50,activation='relu',input_shape=c(1))
layer_dense(model,units=1,activation='linear')
layer_dense(model,units=100,activation='relu')
layer_dense(model,units=1,activation='linear')
compile(model,loss="mean_squared_error",optimizer="nadam")
history <- fit(model,x,y,batch_size=50,epochs=5000,verbose=0)

summary(model)
## ___________________________________________________________________________
## Layer (type)                     Output Shape                  Param #     
## ===========================================================================
## dense_10 (Dense)                 (None, 50)                    100         
## ___________________________________________________________________________
## dense_11 (Dense)                 (None, 1)                     51          
## ___________________________________________________________________________
## dense_12 (Dense)                 (None, 100)                   200         
## ___________________________________________________________________________
## dense_13 (Dense)                 (None, 1)                     101         
## ===========================================================================
## Total params: 452
## Trainable params: 452
## Non-trainable params: 0
## ___________________________________________________________________________
plot(x,y,type="l")
lines(x,predict(model,x),col="blue",lty=2)
